course.subject: OCES
course.name: Chemical Oceanography
course.description: This course focuses on the major biogeochemical processes in the coastal, benthic, and upper ocean pelagic ecosystems that control the abundances, distribution and transformation of chemical substances. The impacts of human activities and climate change on these processes will be discussed. The use of isotope tracers as a tool to investigate the age and sources of water masses will be illustrated.
course.prerequisites: OCES 2001 AND OCES 2002
